  "text": "In addition to the signal models, the node distribution also affects both performance and complexity of FSD. Although it is difficult to provide a comprehensive analysis of the node distribution to achieve optimal performance, a general method proposed in [CITATION_1] could be used for an arbitrary constellation and for any number of antennas. The number of visited child nodes of each parent node in one level can be chosen from a small set {1, N b }, where N b is the number of branches per node. In the top levels, a full search is performed by visiting all the N b branches, whereas in the lower levels, only one branch is chosen as survivor [CITATION_2] . When combined with the SQRD, this method guarantees that the nodes with highest signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) are firstly visited. In this paper we adopt this kind of node distribution together with the SQRD to maximize the BER performance, with an exception for the case with 64-QAM modulation and list size = 128.",
